profile_positions.description:
This company works on Master Planning, Landscape Architecture and Architecture. Our team consisted of 15 persons with varying backgrounds such as landscape architects, architects, landscape designers and civil technical engineers. As a Master Planning Landscape Architect my position within the company was to serve directly to the two owners/directors and to manage the rest of the staff. 
- I set out the main lines and structure in company, such as instituting a data management system, the layout for projects including internal budgets and external invoices; 
- Supervision of all running and coming projects to guarantee total execution and watched over budgets and deadlines by work meetings and reports. 
- The projects varied from roof gardens till Regional Master Planning projects.
- By content I was mainly responsible for the concepts and designs. Besides that I led the process to detailing, total documentation and execution including assistance in the logistics and application of (new) materials; 
- One or two days per week I was on the road to hand in projects or to discuss them with our clients and to acquire new projects;
- I checked the right execution of projects by contractors to guarantee the desired end goal. That’s why I was the direct contact for all participants in every project.
